deck: Father Caedius is the 400 year old leader of Hinterland, a station on the planet Sullen Dun.
description:
Origin

Olin Caedius was the oldest Magic Priest alive and offered a job on the planet Sullen Dun, where demons (who regularly attacked the Earth) came from. He accepted the job, taking a group of Magic Priests and Warrior Nuns with him.

Major Story Arcs

On the planet Sullen Dun stands a fort called Hinterland, where Magic Priests and Warrior Nuns monitor demon activity and report back to Earth. After fellow Warrior Nuns are wrongly accused of murder, they are transported back to Earth. Now the last Warrior Nun present, Dei confronts Olin Caedius about the wrong accusations of her former teammates. Their discussion causes Olin to break into a fury in which he tells Dei God doesn't exist and casts her out of Hinterland. She is immediately attacked by demons and taken back to the demon lair. In retaliation, Magic Priests attack the demon lair, take their leader Ramus and burn down the lair. Dei is left for dead inside the lair. She manages to escape however, and is taken back to Hinterland by Ramus' former spy Futz. There she witnesses Olin Caedius, who has taken Ramus' designs (as Ramus had planned) and cloned a new army of Magic Priests, taking a rocket ship back to Earth with the clones. Warrior Nun Dei puts on her space armor and follows the ship from a distance Hyperjumping in space, the rocket ships makes a bump, which releases the clones. The clones attack Olin Caedius who shoots them with his flamethrower. These clones have, unbeknownst to Olin Caedius, toxic skins. Because of their toxic skins, the ship explodes in space, killing Olin Caedius. Warrior Nun Dei is caught in the blast.

A research team concludes that, if Caedius would have managed to reach the Earth, the clones would have killed half the Earth's population within two weeks. Caedius is deemed a traitor to the church.
name: Olin Caedius

deck: Warrior Nun Dei is the last Warrior Nun on Hinterland, a station on the planet Sullen Dun, where demons come from.
description:
Origin

Nothing much is known about Dei's origin, except that she volunteered for duty on the planet Sullen Dun and wanted to make a difference. Still believing in God, she often came into conflict with the head Magic Priest Olin Caedius.

Major Story Arcs

On the planet Sullen Dun stands a fort called Hinterland, where Magic Priests and Warrior Nuns monitor demon activity and report back to Earth. After fellow Warrior Nuns are wrongly accused of murder, they are transported back to Earth. Now the last Warrior Nun present, Dei confronts Olin Caedius about the wrong accusations of her former teammates. Their discussion causes Olin to break into a fury in which he tells Dei God doesn't exist and casts her out of Hinterland. She is immediately attacked by demons and taken back to the demon lair. In retaliation, Magic Priests attack the demon lair, take their leader Ramus and burn down the lair. Dei is left for dead inside the lair. She manages to escape however, and is taken back to Hinterland by Ramus' former spy Futz. There she witnesses Olin Caedius, who has taken Ramus' designs (as Ramus had planned) and cloned a new army of Magic Priests, taking a rocket ship back to Earth with the clones. Warrior Nun Dei puts on her space armor and follows the ship from a distance Hyperjumping in space, the rocket ships makes a bump, which releases the clones. The clones attack Olin Caedius who shoots them with his flamethrower. These clones have, unbeknownst to Olin Caedius, toxic skins. Because of their toxic skins, the ship explodes in space, killing Olin Caedius. Warrior Nun Dei is caught in the blast.

A research team concludes that, if Caedius would have managed to reach the Earth, the clones would have killed half the Earth's population within two weeks. Caedius is deemed a traitor to the church.

On Earth, Dei receives the highest honor a Warrior Nun can receive. Her funeral speech is delivered by the the Pope himself.

deck: A detection dog who works at Los Angeles International Airport
description:
Origin

Trained as a detection dog after being adopted from a shelter, Pretzels was assigned to work searching for contraband at LAX. He proved very adept, and was singlepawedly responsible for making smuggling through LAX almost impossible.

Creation

Pretzels was created by Nick Spencer and Steve Lieber. He made his first appearance in The Fix #1.

Major Story Arcs

The Fix

Pretzels becomes the target of Roy and Mac, who have been tasked with smuggling something through customs. He is partnered with Mac, to whom he takes an instant dislike. However, after they take down a drug smuggler together, Pretzels bonds with Mac. He is seriously wounded during an attempt to apprehend a suspicious person in the airport, but manages to survive.

Powers and Abilities

Pretzels is a highly-trained and very skilled detection dog.
name: Pretzels the Dog

deck: A member of the Suicide Squad. Killed in Action on a mission.
description:
Origin

Nothing is known about Battleaxe's origin, or how she came to work for the Suicide Squad.

Major Story Arcs

Suicide Squad Most Wanted: Katana

Battleaxe makes an appearnce along with other members of the Squad in Markovia at the same time Katana was there fighting Kobra. The group interevend as she was making her escape from Kobra's forces. The battle was close to won, but Kobra escaped thanks too the Marlovian military's attempts to attack. Once the battle ends, Battleaxe compliments Katana but gets the cold shoulder.

On their move against Kobra's volcano base, Battleaxe and Digger trade banter along the way to their target. When they encounter a patrol, the team takes them out and dons their gear to sneak into the base. Battleaxe is unsre the plan will work, but Katana thinks so, so she decides to go along. They manage to gather intel, but their cover is blown. The group went into a tunnel for cover, but it turns out to be where Kobra is directing the lava flow. They manage to seal the tunnel, but Heatstroke is too fatigued to walk. Katana asks Battleaxe to help, but she refuses until Deadshot orders her to. They reach the end of the tunnel, only to be captured by Kobra forces who have taken over the capital.

While King Kobra gloats over his vistory, Katana and the Squad escape their restraints and try to fight off Kobra's forces. However, Lady Eve gives King Kobra a device that triggers the bombs in the Squad member's necks. He tests it on Battleaxe, killing her and revealing the purpose of the implants to Kobra.

Powers and Abilities

Battleaxe has no actual powers, relying one her close combat skills and the two headed axe that she is named for.

deck: Magnus the Black is a mighty fighter seeking his purpose in the world.
description:
Origin

Magnus is a Viking who comes from a hamlet in Norway called Brakstad. He was a household soldier of the local lord. He fought many battles for his lord. After one such battle, the surviving members of the enemy soldiers came to Magnus' home and burned all there was. In the end, they had killed his wife.

After his wife had died, Magnus looked at the world around him. He saw the world changing, converting to Christianty, who preached love but enforced it by cruelty. It intrigued him and thus accepted the challenge to take Cardinal Farina up the treacherous Black Road to the north of Norway.

Major Story Arcs

Days into his travel with Cardinal Farina, they were attacked by a group of armed men. Overpowered, Magnus was unable to prevent the men from killing Cardinal Farina. Left for dead, Magnus was found and nursed back to health by Julia, the adopted daughter of Farina. She asked him to go escort her north in Farina's place.

While escorting Julia across the Black Road, Magnus suddenly remembers he had seen Kitta in the battle against enemy soldiers that killed his wife. Telling this to Julia, she points out to Magnus they're being followed by the same Kitta. Suddenly, Julia turns on Magnus and shoots him several times with her crossbow. She escapes north. Kitta takes care of Magnus and offers to join him in tracking down Julia.
